    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in gNB tracer application\n\n### Summary\nThe gNB tracer application (`gnb.c`) had several memory leaks due to an infinite loop that prevented proper cleanup of allocated resources. The application would run indefinitely without freeing:\n- Database allocated with `parse_database()`\n- `is_on` array allocated with `calloc()`\n- OBUF buffer allocated through `PUTC()` calls\n- Socket connections\n- Mutex resources\n\nThis fix adds signal handling for graceful shutdown and proper resource cleanup.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gnb.c`: \n  * Added signal handlers for SIGINT and SIGTERM\n  * Replaced infinite `while(1)` loop with `while(!exit_flag)`\n  * Added cleanup code for socket, buffer, database, array, and mutex\n  * Added proper exit handling to free all allocated resources\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Run the gNB tracer application with a valid database file\n2. Let it run for an extended period while processing trace events\n3. Terminate the application with Ctrl+C\n4. Observe memory not being freed (can be checked with valgrind or similar tools)\n\nThe memory leaks were particularly noticeable during long-running tracing sessions where the OBUF buffer would grow significantly but never be freed.\n"
}